headlines.description: — Quentin Grimes scored 28 points in his first game against his former team and the Philadelphia 76ers beat the Dallas Mavericks 130-125 in a matchup of injury-depleted clubs Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Quentin Grimes scores 28 as Sixers beat Mavs 130-125 in matchup of injury-depleted teams

headlines.description: — Paolo Banchero scored 24 points, Franz Wagner added 22 and the Orlando Magic stunned Cleveland 108-103 on Sunday to end the Cavaliers' winning streak at 16 games.
headlines.shortLinkText: Magic end Cavaliers' winning streak at 16 games as Banchero scores 24 points in 108-103 victory

events.name: Phoenix Suns at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — Luka Doncic had 33 points, 11 rebounds and eight assists, and the Los Angeles Lakers snapped their four-game losing streak with a 107-96 victory over the Phoenix Suns on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Luka Doncic scores 33, Lakers snap their 4-game skid with a 107-96 win over the Suns

headlines.description: — Cam Johnson scored 28 points, Keon Johnson added 22 and the Brooklyn Nets beat the Atlanta Hawks 122-114 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Nets continue home dominance against Hawks with 122-114 victory

events.name: Toronto Raptors at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Anfernee Simons scored 12 of his 22 points in the fourth quarter, Toumani Camara finished with 21 and the Portland Trail Blazers rallied from a 16-point deficit to beat the Toronto Raptors 105-102 on Sunday to snap a five-game skid.
headlines.shortLinkText: Simons scores 22, Camara adds 21 as Blazers hit 18 3-pointers and beat the Raptors 105-102

headlines.description: — Anthony Edwards scored 41 points on Sunday as the Minnesota Timberwolves won their eighth straight, beating the Utah Jazz 128-102.
headlines.shortLinkText: Edwards drops 41 as Wolves win eighth straight, 128-102 over skidding Jazz

headlines.description: — James Harden had 31 points and 10 rebounds, Kawhi Leonard scored 23 points and the Los Angeles Clippers beat Charlotte 123-88 Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Harden records a double-double to send Clippers past sluggish Charlotte 123-88

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Milwaukee Bucks

headlines.description: — Shai Gilgeous-Alexander had 31 points and eight assists as the Western Conference-leading Oklahoma City Thunder defeated the Milwaukee Bucks 121-105 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gilgeous-Alexander scores 31 as Thunder beat Bucks 121-105 for 10th win in last 11 games
